quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  41,19,"On the Day that the enemies of God shall be gathered together and driven to the Fire, they shall be formed into groups, and"
  41,20,"when they come close to it, their ears, eyes and skins will testify against them for their misdeeds"
  41,21,"And they will ask their skins, \"Why did you bear witness against us?\" and their skins will reply, \"God, who gives speech to all things, has given speech to us [as well], it was He who created you in the first instance and to Him you are [now] brought back"
  41,22,"you could not hide yourselves from your ears and your eyes and your skins to prevent them from testifying against you, and you thought that God would never know much of what you did"
  41,23,"but these thoughts which you entertained concerning your Lord, have brought you to destruction, and [now] you are among the utterly lost"
  41,24,"Even if they are patient, the Fire will still be their homes. And if they pray to be allowed to make amends, they will not be allowed to do so"
  41,25,"We assigned to them companions who made their doings appear fair to them. But the same decree [of punishment] proved true against them, which had proved true against nations of jinn and mankind who passed away before them. Surely they were the losers"